message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "cce-ruby: Code Context Engine (Ruby implementation)"
abstract: >-
  A local command-line Code Context Engine: it AST-chunks a source-code
  repository with tree-sitter, embeds each chunk, stores a vector and keyword
  index on disk, and answers queries with hybrid vector + BM25 retrieval. A
  clean-room, test-first Ruby implementation of the shared specification
  (SPEC v1.0), extended cumulatively with a metrics/observability dashboard
  (v1.1), pluggable per-language packs (SPEC v2.0), secret-scrubbing indexing
  (SPEC v2.1), workspaces of related codebases (SPEC v2.2), an optional
  offline-first, content-addressed sync cache over a git remote (SPEC-SYNC,
  v2.3), and a Model Context Protocol server so an agent (Claude Code) uses CCE
  as a native tool (SPEC-MCP, v2.4). Runs fully offline apart from installing the
  gem, the optional local Ollama embedder, and git-transported sync push/pull.
